  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 1 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 5 high, 5 medium, 29 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI); plus 2 other bases. 5 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, low cloud base and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF). Primary drivers: RVR limitations, cold‑temperature performance penalties and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Josep Tarradellas Barcelona-El Prat (BCN/LEBL), Adolfo Suárez Madrid–Barajas (MAD/LEMD) and 9 others.",
